title: Warner Bros. Discovery sues Paramount over 'South Park' streaming rights
description: Warner Bros. Discovery sued Paramount on Friday over the streaming rights for cartoon comedy "South Park" on HBO Max.

title: Mark Zuckerberg announces Meta's new large language model as A.I. race heats up
description: The model, called LLaMA, is intended to help scientists and engineers explore applications for AI such as answering questions and summarizing documents.

title: Haunting photos show a year of Russia's war in Ukraine
description: A selection of images shows Russia's war in Ukraine on the one-year anniversary of the invasion.

title: Luxury EV maker Lucid appears to have a demand problem
description: Lucid plans to build just 10,000 to 14,000 vehicles in 2023, despite factory capacity to build more.

title: 'I really want to go back to fight:' A wounded Ukrainian soldier reflects on his recovery
description: Roman Horodenskyi, a double amputee as a result of Russia's war in Ukraine, shares his story of recovery.

title: Ericsson to lay off 8,500 workers as part of cost-cutting plan
description: It will impact roughly 8% of Ericsson's staff of 105,529 worldwide.

title: Biden's IRA is the U.S. playing 'catch-up' after Trump, UK minister says
description: The U.K.'s Finance Minister said Friday that the U.S. Inflation Reduction Act is U.S. President Joe Biden's attempt to play "catch-up" on clean energy investments.

title: Key Fed inflation measure rose 0.6% in January, more than expected
description: The core PCE price index was expected to increase 0.5% from a month ago and 4.4% on an annual basis, according to Dow Jones.

title: Britain's taxes will be cut 'as soon as we can afford to,' finance minister says
description: U.K. Finance Minister Jeremy Hunt on Friday said that the government will look to cut taxes "as soon as we can afford to."

title: Another smartphone supports satellite connectivity, as mobile space race heats up
description: Connecting to satellites allows messages to reach broad swathes of land not captured by earth-based cellular equipment.

title: Ukrainian refugees could help Germany's labor market, but not for long: They're 'ready to go home'
description: Many Ukrainians want to go home as soon as they can, making their participation in Germany's labor market limited and short-term.

title: China again calls for ceasefire on anniversary of the Russia-Ukraine war
description: Marking the one-year mark since Russia invaded Ukraine, China's foreign ministry reiterated its push for the two countries to hold peace talks.

title: 'Business is very good, unfortunately': Arms fair spotlights bonanza year ahead for weapons companies
description: Over the last week, Abu Dhabi's biennial international defense exhibition, known as IDEX, showcased a bustling sector.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Stocks rebound from lows but remain volatile amid confusing market
description: Stocks ended in the green on Thursday, snapping a losing streak. But both investors and analysts are still trying to make sense of the markets.

title: After a year of death and destruction, Ukraine braces itself for a major escalation in the war
description: Russia is expected to launch a large-scale offensive, with Ukraine expected to counter-attack in summer. In the meantime, it's waiting for more weapons.

title: OECD says global economic outlook 'slightly better' for 2023 but inflation risks linger
description: OECD Secretary-General Mathias Cormann said the global economic outlook is looking slightly "brighter" for this year but inflation challenges remain.

title: China's online shoppers started the year cautiously, Alibaba says
description: Online sales remained weak this year through early February, Alibaba CEO Daniel Zhang said during a quarterly earnings call.

title: These high school sweethearts have visited 112 countries. Here's how they pay for it on a budget
description: Hudson and Emily Crider are on a mission to travel to all 195 countries. Here's what it costs and how they spend wisely around the world.

title: A year into the war, Ukraine and the West prepare for the biggest reconstruction since World War II
description: One year since Russia's full-scale invasion, Ukraine's economy and infrastructure are in tatters, with the government and its allies planning the largest rebuilding effort since World War II.

title: SEC rebuffs Elon Musk's attempt to get out of 'funding secured' settlement
description: The SEC argued that "Musk waived his opportunity to test the Commission's allegations at trial when he voluntarily agreed (twice) to a consent judgment."
